# deployments — hardhat-deploy's local artifacts.
#  - Dev networks (localhost / hardhat / devnet fork) are regenerated by every deploy → ignored.
#  - Real networks (sepolia / mainnet) are one-time / irreplaceable → COMMITTED. The Sepolia
#    freeze was executed via the Safe UI, so hardhat-deploy never produced records for it; the
#    committed set under deployments/sepolia is reconstructed for the frozen core (addresses
#    verified on-chain + against docs/CHAINS.md) plus genuine records for the redeployable views.
#  - solcInputs/ (per-deploy verification blobs) stay ignored — bulky and regenerable from source.
# deployedContracts.ts + docs/CHAINS.md remain the human/client source of truth (ADR-0037/0061).
deployments/*
!deployments/sepolia/
!deployments/mainnet/
deployments/sepolia/solcInputs/
deployments/mainnet/solcInputs/

# Safe-native deploy hand-off artifacts (safe-batches.json) — durable, regenerable, per-run; not committed
deploy-state/
# Decoded Safe Transaction Builder upload files (regenerated from safe-batches.json per batch)
*-txbuilder.json

# typescript
*.tsbuildinfo

